The paper proposes a new algorithm for local causal discovery in a causal network, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is designed to be efficient, which is a common concern in machine learning and data science (cs.LG, cs.DS). The algorithm also involves conditional independence tests, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on Bayesian networks, which is a common topic in statistical inference and machine learning (cs.SI).
